Package es.ull.isaatc.simulation.sequential.flow

Classes required to define workflows.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
FinalizerFlow A flow which finishes an execution branch.
Flow The process an element has to carry out.
InitializerFlow A flow which begins an execution branch.
JoinFlow A finalizer flow which merges several incoming branches into one.
SplitFlow A initializer flow which can create several outgoing branches.
TaskFlow A flow which executes some kind of work.
 

Class Summary
ANDJoinFlow A merge flow which allows only one of the incoming branches to pass.
BasicFlow Basic implementation of a flow.
ConditionalFlow A multiple successor flow whose successors are conditioned, that is, the successor can only be activated if the condition is met.
DiscriminatorFlow An AND join flow which allows only the first true incoming branch to pass.
DoWhileFlow A structured loop flow which resembles a do-while loop.
ExclusiveChoiceFlow A conditional flow which allows only one of the outgoing branches to be activated.
ForLoopFlow A structured loop flow which resembles a for loop.
GeneralizedMergeFlowControl  
InterleavedParallelRoutingFlow A structured flow which contains a set of activities which must be performed according to a predefined set of partial orderings.
InterleavedRoutingFlow A structured flow whose initial step is a parallel flow and whose final step is a synchronization flow.
MergeFlow A flow which merges several incoming branches into a single outgoing branch.
MergeFlowControl Control of incoming branches per element.
MultiChoiceFlow A conditional flow which allows all outgoing branches which meet their condition to be activated.
MultiMergeFlow Creates an OR flow which allows all the true incoming branches to pass.
MultipleSuccessorFlow A flow with multiple successors.
ORJoinFlow A merge flow which allows all the true incoming branches to pass.
ParallelFlow A multiple successor flow which creates a new work thread per outgoing branch.
PartialJoinFlow An AND join flow which allows only the n-st true incoming branch to pass.
PredefinedStructuredFlow An structured flow with predefined both entry and exit points.
ProbabilitySelectionFlow A flow which selects one outgoing branch among a set of them by using a probability value.
SafeMergeFlowControl  
SimpleMergeFlow Creates an OR flow which allows all the true incoming branches to pass.
SingleFlow A flow which executes a single activity.
SingleSuccessorFlow A flow with a unique successor.
StaticPartialJoinMultipleInstancesFlow Meets the Static Partial Join for Multiple Instances pattern (WFP34) if acceptValue > 1 and acceptValue < nInstances.
StructuredDiscriminatorFlow A structured flow whose initial step is a parallel flow and whose final step is a discriminator flow.
StructuredFlow A flow which can contain other flows.
StructuredLoopFlow A structured flow which defines a repetitive subflow.
StructuredPartialJoinFlow A structured flow whose initial step is a parallel flow and whose final step is a partial join flow.
StructuredSynchroMergeFlow A structured flow whose initial step is a multi-choice flow and whose final step is a synchronization.
SynchronizationFlow An AND join flow which passes only when all the incoming branches have been activated once.
SynchronizedMultipleInstanceFlow Meets the Multiple Instances with a Priori Design-Time Knowledge pattern (WFP13)
ThreadMergeFlow A flow which merges a specified amount of work threads.
ThreadSplitFlow A flow which creates several instances of the current work thread.
WhileDoFlow A structured loop flow which resembles a while-do loop.
